    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-03-22T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-03-22T12:00:00-05:00" n="646"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d646">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/867: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-03-22T17:00:00+00:00"
                            >March 22, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 22—12:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>161. A journalist has just informed me Ambassador Yoshida had told him this
                    morning that in spite of every desire on the part of Sato<note n="16"
                        xml:id="d646fn16">Naotake Sato, Japanese Minister for Foreign Affairs,
                        replacing Hayashi who replaced Arita.</note> to meet the English,
                    nevertheless, due to strength of the naval party, Japan will not accept 14-inch
                    gun calibre limitation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
